<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4496346>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 15. A–F: Maladera formosae (Brenske, 1898) (Taiwan: Amping); G–K: M. ovatula (Fairmaire, 1891) (China: Sichuan: Wolong); L–P: M. hongkongica (Brenske, 1898) (China: Guangdong: Dinghu). A, G, L: aedeagus, left side lateral view; E, J, O: aedeagus, right side lateral view; B, H, M: aedeagus, dorsal view; C, D, I, N: aedeagus, dorsal view; F, K, P: habitus. Scale: 0.5 mm. Habitus not to scale." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4496346/files/figure.png" .

